node.text:
I dedicate my performance in the @mlb #CelebrityAllstar game to my father who never played catch w/ me growing up. 🤣 (swipe) 

Fathers please play catch w/ your sons so they don’t suck a softball when they grow up. Still had a lot of fun
🤦🏾‍♂️🤷🏾‍♂️🤣

Catch the game tonight on @espn 

Video caught by my son @rachelssideburns who I never played catch with lol 🤣🤣🤣

node.text:
A lot of people know me as the guy who can get people to look inward, face hard truths and get real with themselves. But sometimes what is easy to forget is that doing my “day job” means I have to be away from some of the people I love most – and that can be really hard, especially when it comes to wanting to stay involved in my son’s life. Being busy doing what you love is always great, but unfortunately it sometimes comes at the cost of seeing the ones you love.
With Father’s Day coming up, while I’m off on location shooting, it amplifies these emotions even more – but we try to combat that by making the effort and being mindful about staying connected. Even though it's been harder to be apart than both of us would like to admit, and we cherish the moments we can spend together – and we have fun doing it! 
We’ve come a long way from me waiting in the payphone line at school, and thanks to @portalfromfacebook, it still feels like we are right next to each other - whether that’s to tell each other we love one another or learn a new viral dance together! 
And get to stay connected even when we’re apart. #ShareSomethingReal #PortalPartner
